---
import ClerriLayout from '../../layouts/ClerriLayout.astro';
---
<ClerriLayout title="Leadership Mandate" section="leadership-mandate">

<div class="page-head">
  <div class="page-eyebrow">Strategy · Leadership Direction</div>
  <h1 class="page-title">The mandate from <em>Jim + Judd.</em></h1>
  <p class="page-sub">What leadership empowered, how they expect you to operate, and what they prioritized — captured from the CEO/President alignment on 2026-06-01. This is the north star everything else ladders to.</p>
</div>

<div class="page-body">

  <div class="takeaway">
    <span class="tk-lbl">Bottom line</span>
    <p>Overwhelmingly empowering: full authority to rebuild the team + own all comms, and leadership independently reached the same vendor conclusions you had. The core expectation isn't a task list — it's an operating style: <strong>own it, move fast, present options + a recommendation, never surprise them.</strong> The #1 strategic mandate is direct-to-patient membership marketing — wrapped in a hard anti-kickback compliance guardrail.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="progress-track"><div class="progress-fill" data-progress-fill="leadership-mandate"></div></div>
  <p class="mono" style="font-size:0.75rem;color:var(--muted)">Mandate items actioned: <span data-progress-here="leadership-mandate">0 / 0</span></p>

  <h2>Authority you were granted</h2>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card"><h4>Rebuild the team</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Full authority to manage and rebuild marketing — including replacing people who can't grow. Jim was openly dissatisfied with current scope/flexibility.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Own all comms + PR</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Every press release routes through marketing for voice consistency (triggered by the Cherry PR going out without you). You own the PR Newswire relationship.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Cut underperforming vendors</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Terminate regardless of contract status, with Judd/CFO as your negotiating leverage. New company policy: <strong>no multi-year contracts</strong>.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Automate-first hiring</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Build AI agents instead of rubber-stamp roles. Prioritize a "marketing engineer." Evaluate Nik for that permanent seat.</p></div>
  </div>

  <h2>How they expect you to operate <em>(this is the real expectation).</em></h2>
  <div class="callout zest-hi">
    <ol style="margin:0;padding-left:1.2rem;font-size:0.95rem;line-height:1.7">
      <li><strong>Owner's mindset</strong> — clean <em>and</em> organize at the same time; don't wait for a perfect process.</li>
      <li><strong>First principles + speed</strong> — a 50%-solution shipped fast beats a perfect one later.</li>
      <li><strong>Options + recommendation, never isolation</strong> — don't ask permission for everything, don't go dark either. Bring "here's what I found, 2-3 options, my rec, what I'm doing unless you object."</li>
      <li><strong>Over-communicate / no surprises</strong> — speed balanced with trust + attention to detail. Jim's weekly call is the venue.</li>
      <li><strong>Route by person</strong> — Jim = customer messaging/positioning; Jacob = systems/process; Judd = money/contracts.</li>
    </ol>
  </div>

  <h2>The #1 mandate — <em>and its landmine.</em></h2>
  <p style="color:var(--ink-soft);max-width:70ch"><strong>Direct-to-patient membership marketing is the priority.</strong> Previous teams failed at it; Jim wants automated patient email campaigns, expanding from cash-pay to <em>all</em> patients, because front-desk staff can't be relied on to sell. This is your headline deliverable — see the <a href="/clerri/segment-plan">Segment Marketing Plan</a>.</p>
  <div class="callout wine">
    <div class="lbl">⚠️ The compliance guardrail — non-negotiable</div>
    <p style="margin:0">For member outreach, Clerri must act like an <strong>insurance company</strong> from a regulatory standpoint. Anti-kickback laws mean you <strong>inform</strong> patients about membership options, never <strong>incentivize</strong>. Jim + Judd flagged this twice. This is the one place "move fast / 50% solution" can create legal exposure — so <strong>get the guardrails defined with legal FIRST, then move fast within them.</strong></p>
  </div>

  <h2>What this validates</h2>
  <div class="callout mint">
    <p style="margin:0">Leadership reached the same conclusions you had — you're ahead of where they expected: <strong>vendor cleanup</strong> (multi-year ban + CFO leverage), <strong>7knots in-house</strong> (Jim's been hand-fixing newsletters himself), <strong>Opascope too expensive</strong> (you told them; they agree), <strong>Loudspeaker in-house</strong>, the <strong>marketing-engineer</strong> role + evaluating Nik, and the <strong>AEO/LLM identity fix</strong> via re-released historical PRs. The work in this hub is aligned with leadership, not ahead of its skis.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>Tensions to manage</h2>
  <div class="grid-2">
    <div class="card"><h4>Team pressure vs. fair evaluation</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Jim wants movement on the team, but you've barely met them. Do fair 1:1 assessments this week before any personnel call — you have authority, but a rushed cut violates "attention to detail / build trust."</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Patient marketing overlaps Jacob's team</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Product already runs customer campaigns. Coordinate with Nik + Jacob on list accuracy so you don't message customers as prospects (the botched-campaign risk).</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Speed vs. detail</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">Resolve by axis: move fast on reversible things, over-communicate on visible/irreversible ones.</p></div>
    <div class="card"><h4>Autonomy vs. no-surprises</h4><p style="font-size:0.9rem">They want you to decide AND tell them. Default to the options+recommendation framing in the weekly call.</p></div>
  </div>

  <h2>Triaged task list</h2>
  <h3>This week (leadership-visible)</h3>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-01-1on1s" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">1:1s with Liz, Diamond, Mike + audit blog/social during them</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-02-invoices" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Send all vendor invoices to Judd (Airbase spend review)</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-03-prnewswire" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Finalize + share the PR Newswire contract to Jim/Judd</div></div></label></div>

  <h3>Near-term (the mandate)</h3>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-04-compliance" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Define patient-outreach compliance guardrails with legal BEFORE building campaigns</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-05-vendors" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Vendor meetings: Opascope, 7 Knots, Verve (toward termination post-migration)</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-06-emails" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">5 marketing-email ideas → John; Liz collects historical PRs (LLM play); trade-show list from Diamond</div></div></label></div>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-07-segments" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Build out the segment marketing plan (SMB / Enterprise / Patient)</div></div></label></div>

  <h3>Awareness</h3>
  <div data-section="leadership-mandate"><label class="task"><input type="checkbox" data-track="lm-08-board" data-section="leadership-mandate" /><div class="task-content"><div class="task-title">Board meeting, Salt Lake City, Thursday 6/4 — in-person planning after</div></div></label></div>

  <div class="note-block">
    <div class="note-label">Mandate notes <span class="note-saved">✓ saved</span></div>
    <textarea data-note="leadership-mandate-notes" placeholder="Updates as the weekly call happens, decisions made, where leadership steers differently..."></textarea>
  </div>

  <div class="topic-foot">
    <a href="/clerri/foundation"><span class="dir">← Prev</span><span class="name">Strategic Foundation</span></a>
    <a href="/clerri/segment-plan"><span class="dir">Next →</span><span class="name">Segment Marketing Plan</span></a>
  </div>

</div>
</ClerriLayout>
